annotationA: Protein sarah; Required for elongation of meiosis I spindle. Critical for ovulation, meiotic progression in oocytes and female courtship behavior, including their postmating changes. Regulates female meiosis by controlling calcineurin activity in the germline. Has a role in calcium signaling during egg activation; bcd mRNA polyadenylation and translation in the oocyte; Belongs to the RCAN family
annotationB: Ras association family member; Protein binding; zinc ion binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to gamma radiation; negative regulation of signal transduction; regulation of multicellular organism growth
